Rajkot incurs Rs 10cr loss due to rains
RAJKOT: The city has incurred an estimated loss of Rs 10 crore due to damage caused to roads by rains. "While the damage to the roads is estimated to be Rs 10 crore, damage to the public property is yet to be estimated. RMC commissioner Ajay Bhadu has instructed RMC officials and engineers to carry out an extensive survey to ascertain the damage," said an RMC official.